# --- LLM (routed through OpenRouter, same provider Maple uses) ---
# An OpenRouter API key. Re-use the key Maple uses for its chat agent.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# --- Maple API (for the 1:1 "assistant" agent's read-only tools via MCP) ---
# The local Maple API base; the assistant calls ${MAPLE_API_URL}/mcp with the
# internal service token (INTERNAL_SERVICE_TOKEN, read from repo-root .env.local).
MAPLE_API_URL=http://localhost:3472

# --- Electric Agents server (from docker compose) ---
# Where the agents-server is reachable from this Node process.
# (docker-compose publishes the agents-server on host port 4438.)
AGENTS_URL=http://localhost:4438

# --- This app (long-lived webhook + REST server) ---
# Under `bun run dev` this app runs through portless, which assigns a per-worktree
# PORT (4000-4999) and serves it at https://[<worktree>.]agents.localhost. Leave
# PORT and SERVE_URL unset: src/server/index.ts falls back to PORT=4700 standalone
# and always derives SERVE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:${PORT} so the
# agents-server (in Docker) can deliver wakes to this app's /webhook on the actual
# bound port. Only set these if you run without portless and need a fixed port.
# PORT=4700
# SERVE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:4700
